description: For sale: $575,000. Welcome to the charm of Afton! Country feel with convenience of Woodbury and downtown Afton. This property has plenty of space to roam with its 16.68 Acres; add a pole barn, plant gardens or just enjoy the peace and privacy. Spacious 3 car garage with huge walk up attic storage, heated and insulated too. Classic home features main level laundry and ½ bath, 3 bedrooms up; large owners suite includes sitting area, two closets and private bath. Unfinished lower level could be finished with additional bedroom, family room and bath; bring your imagination. Newer windows, upgraded appliances, and utilities. Imagine grill outs on the deck, bonfires & fun in the backyard.  Welcome Home! We are practicing safety and health guidelines put forth by the CDC so you can feel confident about in-person showings which the seller is allowing. We are also happy to offer virtual showings at request.

description: For sale: $2,100,000. Exceptionally rare and exquisite, this rustic farmhouse-inspired rambler will astound you with its fine attention to detail and master craftsmanship of reclaimed wood throughout. Built on a private, heavily wooded 5+ acre lot on Afton's pristine Lake Edith, where peace and serenity abound, this treasured estate offers tranquil lake views from inside out and an endless list of amenities, making it an entertainer's dream. Adorned with stone, wood accents and gable roofs, the front porch is a delightful, warm welcome to the foyer, where you'll instantly discover an abundance of oversized, floor-to-ceiling windows that maximize the breathtaking views of the lake. Embellished with wood paneled ceilings and walls, the vaulted great room is a sanctuary with its stone surround gas fireplace and leads you into the gourmet kitchen, where the ambiance is warm and inviting. Farmhouse light fixtures hang from a beamed wood ceiling, while hickory cabinets surround professional appliances, and a large center island made of threshing floor pine and a striking granite counter offers additional seating next to the informal dining area. Adjacent to this space is a vaulted family room encased in white shiplap with a sliding barn door that allows you to shut out the noise and relax. Another highly desirable amenity is the formal office with sliding glass barn doors and exclusive access to the front porch. And in its own nook of the home is the private main level Owner's suite with peaceful lake views and spa-like en suite with a free-standing soaking tub, tile surround steam shower and double vanity with copper sinks. Further, a walk-thru master closet is conveniently connected to the laundry room, and to round out the main level, a spacious mudroom with gorgeous built-ins provides two access doors to the heated, pull-through garage that makes storing your vehicles and toys a breeze. The two remaining bedrooms serviced by a ¾ Jack & Jill bath can be found in the lower level, and perfect for entertaining, a large recreation room provides a theater system and impressive wet bar, complete with a TV, appliances and wrap-around seating. The walkout then leads to an outdoor oasis nestled in the wooded backyard, where you can enjoy an elevated deck, stamped concrete patios, bonfire pit and an incredibly restored party barn, along with your own dock and some of the best fishing in the Metro. Properties like this are few and far between, clearly an opportunity of a lifetime! Click here for a video tour: https://tours.spacecrafting.com/nvideo-2cqs

description: For sale: $1,450,000. Let LDK Homes build this stunning luxury home with nearly 5,500 finished sq. ft.  Custom designed with amazing quality and details throughout! Perfect home for today's needs. Gourmet kitchen, formal dining room, hardwood floors, beautiful screened porch with fireplace, main level office. You'll notice all the quality & upgraded mill work throughout. Large walk-in pantry, expanded mudroom with built-ins, unique over-sized 3+ car garage, upstairs includes upper level laundry with convenient built ins and folding counters. Expansive bedroom suites and luxury master suite. Amazing lower level with full bar, rare expansive sport court with adjoining exercise room, plus a bonus theater room perfect for entertaining. Amazing location just steps away from the north side of Afton State Park. Other home options also available.

For sale: $450,000. What an amazing opportunity to own an updated historic home on 1 acre in the heart of Afton! This remodeled home boasts Hardie-Board siding, a newer roof, plentiful outdoor entertaining space, a 3 car garage, and much more. The vaulted master suite will give you peaceful retreat, while the upgraded kitchen allows for walk-out entertaining to the patio and deck with water feature. description: For sale: $1,350,000. Pleased to present this luxurious 5bd/5ba custom-built two-story home on acreage with beautiful nature preserve views in the back. Cedar tongue & groove ceiling in the porch. Custom barreled ceiling inside with white oak that's been burned. Home features an 850 sq ft sport court, storage room/bunker under the wrap-around front porch, game area/theater room, loft, and so much more. The garage is over 1,800 sq ft with a floor drain, hot/cold water in the garage and includes a 12 x 25 room on the back that can serve as a gym, woodshop, etc. 400 amp electrical service, wifi Sonos speakers inside and out, and security cameras. Custom knotty alder cabinets with granite in all bathrooms and laundry room. Beautiful coffer ceiling in the master bedroom. Option to convert sport court to the main level mother-in-law suite. Build your dream home with NewCon Homes. Your lot or ours.

For sale: $575,000. Fantastic walkout rambler with STUNNING St Croix River views. Rare Afton neighborhood setting provides the best of both worlds, privacy and neighbors! Main level owner's suite with attached office and full bathroom. Larage open, vaulted living room adjacent to a formal dining room with walls of windows for long scenic views. Good sized kitchen w/breakfast bar and planty of workspace. Main floor laundry. Large family room in the lower level for entertaining, play room, lots of storage + 2nd and 3rd bedrooms as well as a 3/4 bath (with Sauna!). Enjoy the amazing and private lot from the wrap around maintenance free deck or paver patio. Wooded lot, garden and lush lawn (10 zone irrigation). Home pre-inspected, warranty provided & passed septic test.

description: For sale: $1,150,000. Make this rare & historical 32 acre Afton property part of your living legacy.  Boasting beautiful rolling hills & valleys with over 800ft of the famous  Valley Creek trout stream & a large pond, this property holds the true meaning of Robert Burns "Sweet Afton". Conveniently located, close to the city of Afton, three St. Croix river marina's, public beaches, never-ending bike trails, Afton state park, Afton Alps ski-hills, & award-winning schools. Surrounded by the Belwin Conservatory, large estates, beautiful farms & low-density twnships make this a unique & highly sought after setting within a 20min drive from St. Paul. There is an abundance of wildlife of large whitetail deer, turkeys, mallards, geese, bald eagles & three different types of trout swimming in the never freezing natural spring-fed creek. This is a sportsman's & conservationists paradise! The 3 bedroom rambler includes original Anderson windows, original hardwood floors, redwood siding, wood-burning FP.

description: Recently sold: $535,000. Charming 2 story home situated on a gorgeous 5+ acre private lot in Afton.  Enjoy the stunning year round St. Croix River views from almost every room of the house. The home features 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, 2 fireplaces & a 3 season porch. This property has plenty of storage for all your needs- there is a 2 car attached garage, along with an additional detached 2 car garage & workshop. The private 5 acre lot offers a mix of wooded land along with open spaces, perfect for gardening, a hobby farm or room for the kids to play!  There is also an abundance of wildlife that can be seen daily- deer, turkeys, eagles & owls just to name a few. Situated in the Afton Hills neighborhood, this home offers the perfect mix of country living combined with a small neighborhood setting. The home has newer Andersen Windows, furnace, AC & a 2 zone Invisible Fence system for your pets to enjoy.  Just minutes to downtown Afton, offering shopping, dining, Selma's Ice Cream Parlor, playground & boat Marinas!

description: Recently sold: $715,000. Custom-built by Pratt homes, this wonderful home is situated on a sprawling 7-acre lot, where you can enjoy privacy and scenic views year-round.  Nestled in the wooded backyard is a patio outside the walkout lower level and a peaceful screened-in porch above with deck access, where you can entertain or simply relax in the country setting.  And in front of the home, an inviting front porch welcomes you inside to a vaulted foyer next to the formal dining room and an office boasting a stately coffered ceiling.  The functional floor plan then continues to an open great room, kitchen and informal dining space with lots of windows to provide plenty of natural daylight and serene, wooded views in back of the home.  Four bedrooms on the upper level include the spacious master suite with a private full bath, while an additional full bath services the remaining three bedrooms, and the 5th bedroom and ¾ bath can be found in the lower level.  In addition, a floor-to-ceiling, stone surround fireplace is flanked by built-ins in the walkout family room, making this space cozy and comfortable for movie nights, while the wet bar and game room are great for entertaining.  Located in the prestigious Jacob Fahlstrom Preserve of scenic Afton, this lovingly cared for home is sure to provide that much needed peace and tranquility you're looking for.
